    "Name": "Glaive",
    "Details": "<b>Name: <color=#85DBF6>Glaive Medium Tank</color>\nArmor: <color=#85DBF6>Standard </color>\tTechnology: <color=#85DBF6>Inner Sphere</color>\nMovement: <color=#85DBF6>5/8 (Wheeled)</color>\tEngine: <color=#85DBF6>205 Fusion</color></b>\n\nThe Glaive Medium Tank was designed as an affordable alternative to 'Mechs for forces loyal to Duke Robert Kelswa-Steiner and the Isle of Skye. Developed quickly, it was ready for action in 3066, with most components produced locally.\n\nThe Glaive prioritizes firepower over speed and armor, committing over a third of its mass to weaponry. Its primary weapon is a LRM-15 with enhanced accuracy thanks to an Artemis IV Fire Control System. It also gives the tank indirect fire capability, though the laser-guided system will not help it in that case. An ER Large Laser supplements the missile launcher at long range, while a pair of Machine Guns provide short-range defense against infantry and other threats.",
